subproject.description:
(I-1) National capacity to design, implement and monitor policies will be enhanced and programs to realize the social and economic potential of the cultural sector will be developed; (I-2) Mentorship program established to support artists and producers in strategic locations to refine their products/ services; 
(II-1) Fair and effective marketing networks established by groups and associations of artists and producers including ethnic/ indigenous minorities; (II-2) Improved business development service delivery to cultural entrepreneurs by member-based organizations and business development service providers; 
(III-1) Effective and streamlined implementation of trade legislation and export procedures for promising cultural products/ services; (III-2) Integrated competitiveness strategies developed for promising cultural products/ services; (III-3) Infrastructure created to promote cultural products/ services through certification and quality control.

